	painsBodyHtml={`<p>The Tigray war was one of the deadliest conflicts of the 21st century, leaving hundreds of thousands dead and a generation of children orphaned and displaced. Drought and famine return again and again. Across Ethiopia, the wound of the orphan and the grieving runs deep.</p><p>These are not statistics to a Father. They are children He longs to gather. Ethiopia&rsquo;s ancient faith does not need replacing &mdash; it needs to hear that the God it has revered for centuries is a Father to the fatherless, near to the broken-hearted.</p>`}
